hopobject.body: Please wait best drugstore makeup brands for sensitive skin The Air Titan could have dramatically reduced the delay last week at Chicagoland. The start was delayed by mist for almost 90 minutes. Once the race did go off, it made it almost to the halfway point before the sky opened up again. In all, there were two stoppages totaling 6 hours, 30 minutes and winner Matt Kenseth didn't cross the finish line until early Monday morning.
